    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When a term contains a : the search will not succeed.  I have tried with the : escaped, : as well as quoting the term with double quotes and both fail. 
$term = '<a href="http://127.0.0.1:10088/controller/action">http://127.0.0.1:10088/controller/action</a>';
$urlterm = new Zend_Search_Lucene_Index_Term($term, 'url');
$query = new Zend_Search_Lucene_Search_Query_Term($urlterm);
$hits = $index-&gt;find($query);
echo "Hits: " . count($hits) . "\n";  // will return 0
/*however the following works */
$hits = $index-&gt;find('url:"' . $term . '"');
echo "Hits: " . count($hits) . "\n";  // will return 1</p>

